Installation
============

1. On Red Hat Linux (or compatible), install lua and lua-devel (v5.1).
2. Compile lpeg by running
  $ cd lpeg-*
  $ make
3. Copy lpeg.so to /usr/lib64/lua/5.1/
4. Copy re.lua from lpeg-* to /usr/share/lua/5.1/
5. Copy cosmo and cosmo.lua to /usr/share/lua/5.1/
6. Create a link in $HOME/bin pointing to skilldoc-ng.lua


Usage
=====

$ skilldoc-ng.lua skillppfile.ils

This command creates skillppfile.html.


Examples
========

The examples directory contains sample SKILL++ files and their generated
documentation.


